text: Fannegusha Creek is a stream in the U.S. state of Mississippi. It is a tributary to the Pearl River. Fannegusha is a name derived from the Choctaw language purported to mean "tasty squirrel". ==References== Category:Rivers of Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Rankin County, Mississippi Category:Bodies of water of Scott County, Mississippi Category:Tributaries of the Pearl River (Mississippi–Louisiana)
title: Fannegusha Creek (Pearl River tributary)
